<hl>
<seg id=1> Minister of Information Lamo: Demonstrators of "Fire Never Extinguishes" should Not Become Puppet of Foreign Force </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> (Kuala Lumpur) - Mohammad Lamo, Malaysian Minister of Information, said that the persons who took part in the demonstration of "Fire Never Extinguishes" should not become puppet of foreign force to damage our country, on the contrary, they should express their wills in a more intellectual way. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> He said, as compare with the way of violence and making chaos, an intellectual way of expressing wills is more effective. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> According to Malaysia News Agency, after attending a Family Day activity of Ministry of Information yesterday, Mohammad Lamo told news media that government had taken steps to make people express their wills freely. They can use 500 "Speaking Out Centers" set up all around the country to express their ideas and comments to the country in an appropriate channel. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> He said, government would consider the ideas and comments indicated by the people and make improvement to meet the demand of the numerous people. </seg>
<seg id=6> He emphasized that this is the way in democratic countries. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> He also persuaded those demonstrators to give deliberation to the result of their demonstrations. Because since Malaysia's independent 41 years ago, it is the energetic contribution and construction made by our dedicated people all around the country that built up today's prosperity. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> He said, those demonstrators did not think that it was a behavior of betraying country dignity when they got support from foreign force and further rebelled against our government with all their strength. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=9> He indicated:" If foreign people want to invest in Malaysia, we will give them warm welcome; but if they give money to support the demonstrators, we will surely protest against it." </seg>
</p>
